                                            طهماسپ</foreign>
                  </persName>, whose name is introduced as
                                    an inscription on a palace wall in one of the miniatures,<locus n="60">fol. 60</locus>
                  <term/>
                  <term/>
                </p>
              </handNote>
            </handDesc>
            <decoDesc>
              <decoNote type="unwan">
                <p>In four gold-ruled columns, and richly
                                    ornamented with six highly finished ʻUnvāns</p>
              </decoNote>
              <decoNote type="border">Illuminated headings and borders on every page.
                                The broad margins are covered throughout the volume with spirited
                                drawings of wild animals and flowers in gold</decoNote>
              <decoNote type="miniature">
                <p>Includes fourteen miniatures in the best
                                    Persian style</p>
              </decoNote>
            </decoDesc>
